Equipment Setup (Discreetly)Hidden Camera â€“ A small pinhole camera can capture the interviewer's face and questions.AI-powered Earpiece â€“ A tiny Bluetooth earpiece (like those used for covert communication) can relay AI-generated responses to you.Phone â€“ Your phone (hidden in your pocket or bag) runs an AI assistant that listens  processes  and suggests answers in real time.2. AI Tools to UseLive Transcription & Analysis â€“Otter.ai  Whisper AI  or Google Live Transcribe can process speech into text for quick review.Real-time Answer Suggestions â€“ ChatGPT  Claude  or Google Gemini can generate response suggestions based on the conversation.Sentiment Analysis & Tone Adjustment â€“ AI can analyze the interviewerâ€™s tone and suggest whether to be more formal  casual  or detailed.Execution StrategyTriggering AI Responses â€“ A subtle hand movement or foot tap can activate AI processing when you need a response.Pausing for Natural Delivery â€“ Instead of repeating AI output verbatim  rephrase it naturally.Practicing with AI Beforehand â€“ Get used to how AI suggests responses so it feels smooth in real-time.
